\pard\f0\fs28  {\b C.} ×{\b  ruscinonensis} Gren. & Blanc,{\i  Billotia }{\b 1}: 71 (1866) ({\i C. azarolus} ×{\i  monogyna}), is found occasionally with the parents in the W. Mediterranean region. It is like {\b 21} but has thinner, subglabrous or glabrous leaves glossy green above; petioles up to 12 mm; corymb laxer, glabrescent; flowers 13-16 mm in diameter; sepals more acute; fruit 10-15 mm in diameter, less tomentose while young.
